<hr data-start="888" data-end="891">
<h2 data-start="893" data-end="931">3. EXPLAIN (What is Event ID 4688?)</h2>
<p data-start="933" data-end="983"><strong data-start="933" data-end="983">Event ID 4688 = A new process has been created</strong></p>
<p data-start="985" data-end="1003">This log tells us:</p>
<ul data-start="1004" data-end="1102">
<li data-start="1004" data-end="1027">
<p data-start="1006" data-end="1027">Which process started</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1028" data-end="1044">
<p data-start="1030" data-end="1044">Who started it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1045" data-end="1065">
<p data-start="1047" data-end="1065">From which machine</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1066" data-end="1082">
<p data-start="1068" data-end="1082">Parent process</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1083" data-end="1102">
<p data-start="1085" data-end="1102">Command line used</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1104" data-end="1136">Important fields inside the log:</p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="1137" data-end="1387" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="1137" data-end="1156"><tr data-start="1137" data-end="1156"><th data-start="1137" data-end="1145" data-col-size="sm" class="">Field</th><th data-start="1145" data-end="1156" data-col-size="sm" class="">Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="1176" data-end="1387"><tr data-start="1176" data-end="1223"><td data-start="1176" data-end="1195" data-col-size="sm">New_Process_Name</td><td data-start="1195" data-end="1223" data-col-size="sm">The program that started</td></tr><tr data-start="1224" data-end="1277"><td data-start="1224" data-end="1246" data-col-size="sm">Parent_Process_Name</td><td data-start="1246" data-end="1277" data-col-size="sm">The program that started it</td></tr><tr data-start="1278" data-end="1318"><td data-start="1278" data-end="1292" data-col-size="sm">CommandLine</td><td data-start="1292" data-end="1318" data-col-size="sm">The exact command used</td></tr><tr data-start="1319" data-end="1360"><td data-start="1319" data-end="1337" data-col-size="sm">SubjectUserName</td><td data-start="1337" data-end="1360" data-col-size="sm">The user who ran it</td></tr><tr data-start="1361" data-end="1387"><td data-start="1361" data-end="1372" data-col-size="sm">Computer</td><td data-start="1372" data-end="1387" data-col-size="sm">The machine</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 33px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<p data-start="1389" data-end="1397">Example:</p>
<ul data-start="1398" data-end="1481">
<li data-start="1398" data-end="1414">
<p data-start="1400" data-end="1414">powershell.exe</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1415" data-end="1424">
<p data-start="1417" data-end="1424">cmd.exe</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1425" data-end="1439">
<p data-start="1427" data-end="1439">mimikatz.exe</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1440" data-end="1450">
<p data-start="1442" data-end="1450">nmap.exe</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1451" data-end="1461">
<p data-start="1453" data-end="1461">net user</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1462" data-end="1470">
<p data-start="1464" data-end="1470">whoami</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1471" data-end="1481">
<p data-start="1473" data-end="1481">ipconfig</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1483" data-end="1521">These are <strong data-start="1493" data-end="1520">attacker behavior tools</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="1523" data-end="1526">
<h2 data-start="1528" data-end="1545">4. SOC MEANING</h2>
<p data-start="1547" data-end="1580">This event is used for detecting:</p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer"><div tabindex="-1" class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit"><table data-start="1582" data-end="1879" class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)"><thead data-start="1582" data-end="1611"><tr data-start="1582" data-end="1611"><th data-start="1582" data-end="1591" data-col-size="sm" class="">Attack</th><th data-start="1591" data-end="1611" data-col-size="sm" class="">What to look for</th></tr></thead><tbody data-start="1641" data-end="1879"><tr data-start="1641" data-end="1684"><td data-start="1641" data-end="1651" data-col-size="sm">Malware</td><td data-start="1651" data-end="1684" data-col-size="sm">.exe running from Temp folder</td></tr><tr data-start="1685" data-end="1723"><td data-start="1685" data-end="1705" data-col-size="sm">PowerShell attack</td><td data-start="1705" data-end="1723" data-col-size="sm">powershell.exe</td></tr><tr data-start="1724" data-end="1769"><td data-start="1724" data-end="1747" data-col-size="sm">Privilege escalation</td><td data-start="1747" data-end="1769" data-col-size="sm">cmd.exe + net user</td></tr><tr data-start="1770" data-end="1807"><td data-start="1770" data-end="1778" data-col-size="sm">Recon</td><td data-start="1778" data-end="1807" data-col-size="sm">whoami, ipconfig, netstat</td></tr><tr data-start="1808" data-end="1841"><td data-start="1808" data-end="1827" data-col-size="sm">Lateral movement</td><td data-start="1827" data-end="1841" data-col-size="sm">psexec.exe</td></tr><tr data-start="1842" data-end="1879"><td data-start="1842" data-end="1863" data-col-size="sm">Credential dumping</td><td data-start="1863" data-end="1879" data-col-size="sm">mimikatz.exe</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="sticky h-0 select-none end-(--thread-content-margin) self-end"><div class="absolute end-0 flex items-end" style="height: 33px;"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button aria-label="Copy table" class="hover:bg-token-bg-tertiary text-token-text-secondary my-1 rounded-sm p-1 transition-opacity group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:pointer-events-none group-[:not(:hover):not(:focus-within)]:opacity-0"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></span></div></div></div></div>
<p data-start="1881" data-end="1941">So <strong data-start="1884" data-end="1940">4688 is one of the most important SOC detection logs</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1943" data-end="1996">If you master <strong data-start="1957" data-end="1979">4688 + 4624 + 4625</strong>, you can detect:</p>
<ul data-start="1997" data-end="2096">
<li data-start="1997" data-end="2010">
<p data-start="1999" data-end="2010">Brute force</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2011" data-end="2031">
<p data-start="2013" data-end="2031">Account compromise</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2032" data-end="2051">
<p data-start="2034" data-end="2051">Malware execution</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2052" data-end="2077">
<p data-start="2054" data-end="2077">Attacker reconnaissance</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2078" data-end="2096">
<p data-start="2080" data-end="2096">Lateral movement</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2098" data-end="2132">That is already <strong data-start="2114" data-end="2131">real SOC work</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="2134" data-end="2137">
<h2 data-start="2139" data-end="2202">5. INVESTIGATION NOTE (Write This in investigation_notes.md)</h2>
<p data-start="2204" data-end="2214">Copy this:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2216" data-end="3070"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>## Stage 3 — Event ID 4688 (Process Creation Detection)</span><br><br><span>### What Happened</span><br><span>We searched for Windows Security Event ID 4688 in Splunk, which logs newly created processes on Windows systems.</span><br><br><span>### Why This Matters</span><br><span>Event ID 4688 is important because it shows what programs are executed on a system. Attackers use tools like PowerShell, cmd, net, whoami, and mimikatz during attacks. Monitoring this event helps detect attacker activity.</span><br><br><span>### Key Fields Observed</span><br><span>- New_Process_Name</span><br><span>- Parent_Process_Name</span><br><span>- CommandLine</span><br><span>- SubjectUserName</span><br><span>- Computer</span><br><br><span>### SOC Use Case</span><br><span>This event helps detect:</span><br><span>- Malware execution</span><br><span>- PowerShell attacks</span><br><span>- Privilege escalation</span><br><span>- Reconnaissance commands</span><br><span>- Lateral movement tools</span><br><br><span>### Conclusion</span><br><span>Event ID 4688 is a critical log source for detecting attacker behavior and should always be monitored in a SOC environment.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3072" data-end="3075">
