 from the begining. start by explaining the project and remember all the golden rules. make is clear and step by step and simple</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#6d87e1" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button></div></div></div></div><span class="sr-only"><br></span></section><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" data-turn-id="request-69c1ea1b-cc30-838b-8ba6-ab7172298bd3-3" data-testid="conversation-turn-6" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant" style=""><h4 class="sr-only select-none">ChatGPT said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><span class="group/tool-message"><span class="block first:mt-0 relative text-token-text-secondary hover:text-token-text-primary my-1.5"><div class="group start-0 top-0 me-1.5 overflow-hidden mt-1 text-start"><button class="inline-block" style="opacity: 1;"><div class="flex items-center justify-start gap-1"><span class="text-start">Received app response</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ba3792" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></div></button></div></span></span><div class="mt-1 flex flex-wrap gap-2 empty:hidden"></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="62cbe5af-bd92-4229-838b-231219044cd7" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-4-thinking" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="8">Perfect.</p>
<h1 data-start="10" data-end="43">PROJECT 3 — STAGE 3 EXECUTION</h1>
<h2 data-start="44" data-end="74">Windows Log Detection Lab</h2>
<h2 data-start="75" data-end="122"><span role="text">Focus: Detecting <strong data-start="95" data-end="112">Event ID 4688</strong> in Splunk</span></h2>
<p data-start="124" data-end="246">We are restarting this stage properly from the beginning, and we will follow your <strong data-start="206" data-end="222">Golden Rules</strong> strictly in every step.</p>
<hr data-start="248" data-end="251">
<h1 data-start="253" data-end="279">WHAT THIS STAGE IS ABOUT</h1>
<p data-start="281" data-end="405">In this stage, you are learning how a SOC analyst detects <strong data-start="339" data-end="369">process execution activity</strong> in Windows using <strong data-start="387" data-end="404">Event ID 4688</strong>.</p>
<h3 data-start="407" data-end="433">What is Event ID 4688?</h3>
<p data-start="434" data-end="458">Event ID <strong data-start="443" data-end="451">4688</strong> means:</p>
<blockquote data-start="460" data-end="496">
<p data-start="462" data-end="496"><strong data-start="462" data-end="496">A new process has been created</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="498" data-end="537">In simple words, Windows is telling us:</p>
<ul data-start="539" data-end="677">
<li data-start="539" data-end="562">
<p data-start="541" data-end="562">a program was started</p>
</li>
<li data-start="563" data-end="579">
<p data-start="565" data-end="579">who started it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="580" data-end="608">
<p data-start="582" data-end="608">on which system it started</p>
</li>
<li data-start="609" data-end="642">
<p data-start="611" data-end="642">what command may have been used</p>
</li>
<li data-start="643" data-end="677">
<p data-start="645" data-end="677">which parent process launched it</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="679" data-end="821">This is one of the most important Windows security events for SOC analysts because attackers almost always execute something during an attack.</p>
<p data-start="823" data-end="832">Examples:</p>
<ul data-start="833" data-end="1000">
<li data-start="833" data-end="851">
<p data-start="835" data-end="851"><code data-start="835" data-end="851">powershell.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="852" data-end="863">
<p data-start="854" data-end="863"><code data-start="854" data-end="863">cmd.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="864" data-end="878">
<p data-start="866" data-end="878"><code data-start="866" data-end="878">whoami.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="879" data-end="890">
<p data-start="881" data-end="890"><code data-start="881" data-end="890">net.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="891" data-end="907">
<p data-start="893" data-end="907"><code data-start="893" data-end="907">ipconfig.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="908" data-end="933">
<p data-start="910" data-end="933">suspicious <code data-start="921" data-end="927">.exe</code> files</p>
</li>
<li data-start="934" data-end="1000">
<p data-start="936" data-end="1000">attacker tools like credential dumpers or remote execution tools</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1002" data-end="1132">So this stage is about learning how to <strong data-start="1041" data-end="1075">see those executions in Splunk</strong>, understand them, and document them like a real analyst.</p>
<hr data-start="1134" data-end="1137">
<h1 data-start="1139" data-end="1170">WHY THIS STAGE MATTERS IN SOC</h1>
<p data-start="1172" data-end="1192">A real attacker may:</p>
<ul data-start="1193" data-end="1340">
<li data-start="1193" data-end="1210">
<p data-start="1195" data-end="1210">open PowerShell</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1211" data-end="1231">
<p data-start="1213" data-end="1231">run command prompt</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1232" data-end="1262">
<p data-start="1234" data-end="1262">execute enumeration commands</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1263" data-end="1281">
<p data-start="1265" data-end="1281">create new users</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1282" data-end="1300">
<p data-start="1284" data-end="1300">dump credentials</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1301" data-end="1317">
<p data-start="1303" data-end="1317">launch malware</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1318" data-end="1340">
<p data-start="1320" data-end="1340">run scripts silently</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1342" data-end="1394">If you can detect <strong data-start="1360" data-end="1368">4688</strong>, you can begin to answer:</p>
<ul data-start="1396" data-end="1534">
<li data-start="1396" data-end="1407">
<p data-start="1398" data-end="1407">What ran?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1408" data-end="1421">
<p data-start="1410" data-end="1421">Who ran it?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1422" data-end="1452">
<p data-start="1424" data-end="1452">Was it normal or suspicious?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1453" data-end="1488">
<p data-start="1455" data-end="1488">Did it come after a login attack?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1489" data-end="1534">
<p data-start="1491" data-end="1534">Is this part of malware execution or recon?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1536" data-end="1582">That is real <strong data-start="1549" data-end="1581">Tier 1 / Tier 2 SOC thinking</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="1584" data-end="1587">
<h1 data-start="1589" data-end="1603">STAGE 3 GOAL</h1>
<p data-start="1605" data-end="1653">By the end of this stage, you should be able to:</p>
<ul data-start="1655" data-end="1875">
<li data-start="1655" data-end="1691">
<p data-start="1657" data-end="1691">search for Event ID 4688 in Splunk</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1692" data-end="1730">
<p data-start="1694" data-end="1730">identify key fields inside the event</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1731" data-end="1765">
<p data-start="1733" data-end="1765">understand what each field means</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1766" data-end="1808">
<p data-start="1768" data-end="1808">detect suspicious commands and processes</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1809" data-end="1836">
<p data-start="1811" data-end="1836">write investigation notes</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1837" data-end="1875">
<p data-start="1839" data-end="1875">update GitHub documentation properly</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1877" data-end="1880">
<h1 data-start="1882" data-end="1911">GOLDEN RULES FOR THIS STAGE</h1>
<p data-start="1913" data-end="1961">We will follow this structure every single time:</p>
<h2 data-start="1963" data-end="1990">Step Execution Structure</h2>
<p data-start="1991" data-end="2018">For every step, we must do:</p>
<ol data-start="2020" data-end="2422">
<li data-start="2020" data-end="2071">
<p data-start="2023" data-end="2071"><strong data-start="2023" data-end="2034">Command</strong><br data-start="2034" data-end="2037">
Run the exact search or command</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2073" data-end="2125">
<p data-start="2076" data-end="2125"><strong data-start="2076" data-end="2090">Screenshot</strong><br data-start="2090" data-end="2093">
Capture proof of what you see</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2127" data-end="2186">
<p data-start="2130" data-end="2186"><strong data-start="2130" data-end="2141">Explain</strong><br data-start="2141" data-end="2144">
I explain what the command/search means</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2188" data-end="2250">
<p data-start="2191" data-end="2250"><strong data-start="2191" data-end="2206">SOC Meaning</strong><br data-start="2206" data-end="2209">
I explain why it matters in a real SOC</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2252" data-end="2337">
<p data-start="2255" data-end="2337"><strong data-start="2255" data-end="2277">Investigation Note</strong><br data-start="2277" data-end="2280">
We write the analyst note for <code data-start="2313" data-end="2337">investigation_notes.md</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="2339" data-end="2422">
<p data-start="2342" data-end="2422"><strong data-start="2342" data-end="2366">GitHub Documentation</strong><br data-start="2366" data-end="2369">
We write the correct README entry for your project</p>
</li>
</ol>
<hr data-start="2424" data-end="2427">
<h1 data-start="2429" data-end="2450">STRICT GOLDEN RULES</h1>
<p data-start="2452" data-end="2496">We must also keep your strict working rules:</p>
<h2 data-start="2498" data-end="2520">1. Step Freeze Rule</h2>
<p data-start="2521" data-end="2542">We do not rush ahead.</p>
<p data-start="2544" data-end="2558">For each step:</p>
<ul data-start="2559" data-end="2709">
<li data-start="2559" data-end="2572">
<p data-start="2561" data-end="2572">run command</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2573" data-end="2588">
<p data-start="2575" data-end="2588">verify result</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2589" data-end="2606">
<p data-start="2591" data-end="2606">take screenshot</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2607" data-end="2623">
<p data-start="2609" data-end="2623">explain result</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2624" data-end="2650">
<p data-start="2626" data-end="2650">write investigation note</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2651" data-end="2680">
<p data-start="2653" data-end="2680">update GitHub documentation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2681" data-end="2709">
<p data-start="2683" data-end="2709">then move to the next step</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="2711" data-end="2734">2. No Speeding Ahead</h2>
<p data-start="2735" data-end="2790">We do not batch many steps together and assume results.</p>
<p data-start="2792" data-end="2827">We do <strong data-start="2798" data-end="2826">one clean step at a time</strong>.</p>
<h2 data-start="2829" data-end="2866">3. Every Command Must Be Explained</h2>
<p data-start="2867" data-end="2946">Every Splunk search or Linux/Windows command must be explained in simple terms:</p>
<ul data-start="2947" data-end="3031">
<li data-start="2947" data-end="2961">
<p data-start="2949" data-end="2961">what it does</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2962" data-end="2983">
<p data-start="2964" data-end="2983">why we are using it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2984" data-end="3007">
<p data-start="2986" data-end="3007">what output we expect</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3008" data-end="3031">
<p data-start="3010" data-end="3031">why it matters to SOC</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="3033" data-end="3064">4. Analyst Thinking Required</h2>
<p data-start="3065" data-end="3141">You are not just clicking things.<br>
You are learning to think like an analyst.</p>
<p data-start="3143" data-end="3168">For every result, we ask:</p>
<ul data-start="3169" data-end="3264">
<li data-start="3169" data-end="3186">
<p data-start="3171" data-end="3186">Is this normal?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3187" data-end="3208">
<p data-start="3189" data-end="3208">Is this suspicious?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3209" data-end="3230">
<p data-start="3211" data-end="3230">Why does it matter?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3231" data-end="3264">
<p data-start="3233" data-end="3264">What should an analyst do next?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="3266" data-end="3293">5. Screenshot Discipline</h2>
<p data-start="3294" data-end="3370">Every important action must have a screenshot with a professional file name.</p>
<h2 data-start="3372" data-end="3402">6. Documentation Discipline</h2>
<p data-start="3403" data-end="3443">Everything must be written properly for:</p>
<ul data-start="3444" data-end="3491">
<li data-start="3444" data-end="3470">
<p data-start="3446" data-end="3470"><code data-start="3446" data-end="3470">investigation_notes.md</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="3471" data-end="3491">
<p data-start="3473" data-end="3491">GitHub <code data-start="3480" data-end="3491">README.md</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="3493" data-end="3496">
<h1 data-start="3498" data-end="3538">BEFORE WE START: WHAT WE EXPECT TO SEE</h1>
<p data-start="3540" data-end="3593">For this stage to work, your lab should already have:</p>
<ul data-start="3594" data-end="3718">
<li data-start="3594" data-end="3610">
<p data-start="3596" data-end="3610">Splunk running</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3611" data-end="3646">
<p data-start="3613" data-end="3646">Windows logs forwarding to Splunk</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3647" data-end="3672">
<p data-start="3649" data-end="3672">Security logs available</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3673" data-end="3718">
<p data-start="3675" data-end="3718">Event ID 4688 enabled on the Windows system</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3720" data-end="3902">Important note:<br>
Event ID 4688 is not always useful unless <strong data-start="3778" data-end="3807">Process Creation auditing</strong> is enabled, and sometimes <strong data-start="3834" data-end="3858">command-line logging</strong> must also be enabled to get richer details.</p>
<p data-start="3904" data-end="3978">So in this stage, we first verify whether Splunk is receiving 4688 events.</p>
<hr data-start="3980" data-end="3983">
<h1 data-start="3985" data-end="4002">STAGE 3 ROADMAP</h1>
<p data-start="4004" data-end="4043">This is the simple flow we will follow:</p>
<h2 data-start="4045" data-end="4056">Step 3.1</h2>
<p data-start="4057" data-end="4091">Search for Event ID 4688 in Splunk</p>
<h2 data-start="4093" data-end="4104">Step 3.2</h2>
<p data-start="4105" data-end="4148">Open one event and inspect important fields</p>
<h2 data-start="4150" data-end="4161">Step 3.3</h2>
<p data-start="4162" data-end="4195">Identify suspicious process names</p>
<h2 data-start="4197" data-end="4208">Step 3.4</h2>
<p data-start="4209" data-end="4244">Search for common attacker commands</p>
<h2 data-start="4246" data-end="4257">Step 3.5</h2>
<p data-start="4258" data-end="4303">Understand parent-child process relationships</p>
<h2 data-start="4305" data-end="4316">Step 3.6</h2>
<p data-start="4317" data-end="4353">Document findings like a SOC analyst</p>
<p data-start="4355" data-end="4410">Later, if your logs are rich enough, we can also build:</p>
<ul data-start="4411" data-end="4475">
<li data-start="4411" data-end="4423">
<p data-start="4413" data-end="4423">detections</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4424" data-end="4432">
<p data-start="4426" data-end="4432">alerts</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4433" data-end="4447">
<p data-start="4435" data-end="4447">triage logic</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4448" data-end="4475">
<p data-start="4450" data-end="4475">a small incident scenario</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="4477" data-end="4480">
<h1 data-start="4482" data-end="4525">STEP 3.1 — VERIFY EVENT ID 4688 IN SPLUNK</h1>
<p data-start="4527" data-end="4549">Now we begin properly.</p>
<h2 data-start="4551" data-end="4564">1. COMMAND</h2>
<p data-start="4566" data-end="4627">Open <strong data-start="4571" data-end="4600">Splunk Search &amp; Reporting</strong> and run this search first:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="4629" data-end="4695"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>spl</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security EventID=4688</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4697" data-end="4700">
<h2 data-start="4702" data-end="4730">2. WHAT THIS SEARCH MEANS</h2>
<p data-start="4732" data-end="4760">Let me break it down simply:</p>
<ul data-start="4762" data-end="4939">
<li data-start="4762" data-end="4796">
<p data-start="4764" data-end="4796"><code data-start="4764" data-end="4773">index=*</code><br data-start="4773" data-end="4776">
Search all indexes</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4798" data-end="4881">
<p data-start="4800" data-end="4881"><code data-start="4800" data-end="4836">sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security</code><br data-start="4836" data-end="4839">
Only look at Windows Security Event Logs</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4883" data-end="4939">
<p data-start="4885" data-end="4939"><code data-start="4885" data-end="4899">EventID=4688</code><br data-start="4899" data-end="4902">
Only return process creation events</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="4941" data-end="4973">So this search is asking Splunk:</p>
<blockquote data-start="4975" data-end="5046">
<p data-start="4977" data-end="5046">“Show me every Windows Security log where a new process was created.”</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="5048" data-end="5051">
<h2 data-start="5053" data-end="5086"><span role="text">3. WHY WE START WITH <code data-start="5077" data-end="5086">index=*</code></span></h2>
<p data-start="5088" data-end="5167">We use <code data-start="5095" data-end="5104">index=*</code> first because we are <strong data-start="5126" data-end="5166">verifying where the logs are landing</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="5169" data-end="5270">At this early step, we do not want to assume the logs are only in <code data-start="5235" data-end="5243">lab_dc</code> or another specific index.</p>
<p data-start="5272" data-end="5294">This helps us confirm:</p>
<ul data-start="5295" data-end="5378">
<li data-start="5295" data-end="5323">
<p data-start="5297" data-end="5323">whether 4688 exists at all</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5324" data-end="5352">
<p data-start="5326" data-end="5352">which hosts are sending it</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5353" data-end="5378">
<p data-start="5355" data-end="5378">which index contains it</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="5380" data-end="5412">Later, we can narrow the search.</p>
<hr data-start="5414" data-end="5417">
<h2 data-start="5419" data-end="5440">4. EXPECTED RESULT</h2>
<p data-start="5442" data-end="5474">We expect to see events showing:</p>
<ul data-start="5475" data-end="5574">
<li data-start="5475" data-end="5491">
<p data-start="5477" data-end="5491"><code data-start="5477" data-end="5491">EventID=4688</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="5492" data-end="5503">
<p data-start="5494" data-end="5503">host name</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5504" data-end="5515">
<p data-start="5506" data-end="5515">user name</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5516" data-end="5530">
<p data-start="5518" data-end="5530">process name</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5531" data-end="5551">
<p data-start="5533" data-end="5551">maybe command line</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5552" data-end="5574">
<p data-start="5554" data-end="5574">maybe parent process</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="5576" data-end="5636">If no events appear, that tells us one of these may be true:</p>
<ul data-start="5637" data-end="5756">
<li data-start="5637" data-end="5679">
<p data-start="5639" data-end="5679">process creation auditing is not enabled</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5680" data-end="5704">
<p data-start="5682" data-end="5704">logs are not forwarded</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5705" data-end="5718">
<p data-start="5707" data-end="5718">wrong index</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5719" data-end="5737">
<p data-start="5721" data-end="5737">wrong sourcetype</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5738" data-end="5756">
<p data-start="5740" data-end="5756">time range issue</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="5758" data-end="5826">That would still be useful because verification is part of SOC work.</p>
<hr data-start="5828" data-end="5831">
<h2 data-start="5833" data-end="5849">5. SCREENSHOT</h2>
<p data-start="5851" data-end="5872">Take a screenshot of:</p>
<ul data-start="5873" data-end="5951">
<li data-start="5873" data-end="5901">
<p data-start="5875" data-end="5901">the full Splunk search bar</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5902" data-end="5922">
<p data-start="5904" data-end="5922">the search results</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5923" data-end="5951">
<p data-start="5925" data-end="5951">the event count if visible</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="5953" data-end="5978">Screenshot file name:</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="5979" data-end="6021"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>stage3-step3-1-4688-search.png</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<p data-start="6023" data-end="6064">Put it in your project screenshot folder.</p>
<hr data-start="6066" data-end="6069">
<h2 data-start="6071" data-end="6093">6. ANALYST QUESTION</h2>
<p data-start="6095" data-end="6141">After you run it, answer this simple question:</p>
<blockquote data-start="6143" data-end="6197">
<p data-start="6145" data-end="6197">Did Splunk return any Event ID 4688 logs, yes or no?</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="6199" data-end="6210">And if yes:</p>
<ul data-start="6211" data-end="6281">
<li data-start="6211" data-end="6255">
<p data-start="6213" data-end="6255">how many results do you see approximately?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="6256" data-end="6281">
<p data-start="6258" data-end="6281">what host names appear?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="6283" data-end="6317">Do not overthink it. Just observe.</p>
<hr data-start="6319" data-end="6322">
<h2 data-start="6324" data-end="6357">7. INVESTIGATION NOTE TEMPLATE</h2>
<p data-start="6359" data-end="6446">Do not paste this yet until you confirm results, but this is the structure we will use:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="6448" data-end="7150"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>## Step 3.1 — Verification of Event ID 4688 in Splunk</span><br><br><span>### Action Performed</span><br><span>Searched Splunk for Windows Security Event ID 4688 using:</span><br><span>`index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security EventID=4688`</span><br><br><span>### Purpose</span><br><span>To verify whether process creation logs are being ingested into Splunk from Windows systems in the lab.</span><br><br><span>### Result</span><br><span>[Write what you observed here]</span><br><br><span>### SOC Meaning</span><br><span>Event ID 4688 is important because it records newly created processes on Windows endpoints and servers. This helps analysts detect suspicious execution activity such as PowerShell abuse, command prompt usage, malware execution, and reconnaissance commands.</span><br><br><span>### Analyst Observation</span><br><span>[Write your short observation here]</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
