<p data-start="332" data-end="371">That means one of these is likely true:</p>
<ol data-start="373" data-end="731">
<li data-start="373" data-end="420">
<p data-start="376" data-end="420"><strong data-start="376" data-end="420">Process Creation Auditing is not enabled</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="421" data-end="471">
<p data-start="424" data-end="471">Splunk is receiving Security logs, but not 4688</p>
</li>
<li data-start="472" data-end="557">
<p data-start="475" data-end="557">The Windows machine has not generated process creation events in the selected time</p>
</li>
<li data-start="558" data-end="599">
<p data-start="561" data-end="599">The time range in Splunk is too narrow</p>
</li>
<li data-start="600" data-end="652">
<p data-start="603" data-end="652">Logs are going to a different sourcetype or index</p>
</li>
<li data-start="653" data-end="731">
<p data-start="656" data-end="731">The system is forwarding logs, but advanced 4688 details are not configured</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p data-start="733" data-end="837">This is normal in labs. We now move into the next proper SOC step: <strong data-start="800" data-end="836">troubleshooting and verification</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="839" data-end="842">
<h1 data-start="844" data-end="916">STEP 3.2 — Confirm Whether Security Logs Are Coming Into Splunk At All</h1>
<p data-start="918" data-end="960">Before we fix 4688, we must first confirm:</p>
<blockquote data-start="962" data-end="1023">
<p data-start="964" data-end="1023">Is Splunk receiving Windows Security logs from the machine?</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="1025" data-end="1164">If yes, then the issue is likely <strong data-start="1058" data-end="1103">Windows audit policy for process creation</strong>.<br data-start="1104" data-end="1107">
If no, then the issue is <strong data-start="1132" data-end="1163">log forwarding or ingestion</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="1166" data-end="1169">
<h2 data-start="1171" data-end="1184">1. COMMAND</h2>
<p data-start="1186" data-end="1217">Run this broader Splunk search:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1219" data-end="1284"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>spl</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1286" data-end="1289">
<h2 data-start="1291" data-end="1318">2. WHAT THIS SEARCH DOES</h2>
<p data-start="1320" data-end="1344">This search asks Splunk:</p>
<blockquote data-start="1346" data-end="1393">
<p data-start="1348" data-end="1393">“Show me any Windows Security events at all.”</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="1395" data-end="1445">We removed <code data-start="1406" data-end="1420">EventID=4688</code> so we can check whether:</p>
<ul data-start="1446" data-end="1543">
<li data-start="1446" data-end="1474">
<p data-start="1448" data-end="1474">Security logs are arriving</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1475" data-end="1505">
<p data-start="1477" data-end="1505">which hosts are sending them</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1506" data-end="1543">
<p data-start="1508" data-end="1543">what kinds of Event IDs are present</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1545" data-end="1548">
<h2 data-start="1550" data-end="1571">3. EXPECTED RESULT</h2>
<p data-start="1573" data-end="1616">You may see common Security Event IDs like:</p>
<ul data-start="1617" data-end="1771">
<li data-start="1617" data-end="1644">
<p data-start="1619" data-end="1644"><code data-start="1619" data-end="1625">4624</code> = successful logon</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1645" data-end="1668">
<p data-start="1647" data-end="1668"><code data-start="1647" data-end="1653">4625</code> = failed logon</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1669" data-end="1686">
<p data-start="1671" data-end="1686"><code data-start="1671" data-end="1677">4634</code> = logoff</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1687" data-end="1725">
<p data-start="1689" data-end="1725"><code data-start="1689" data-end="1695">4672</code> = special privileges assigned</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1726" data-end="1771">
<p data-start="1728" data-end="1771"><code data-start="1728" data-end="1734">4771</code> = Kerberos pre-authentication failed</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1773" data-end="1879">If these appear, then Security logging is working and the issue is likely just <strong data-start="1852" data-end="1878">4688 not being enabled</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="1881" data-end="1960">If this also returns 0 events, then we may have a forwarding or source problem.</p>
<hr data-start="1962" data-end="1965">
<h2 data-start="1967" data-end="1983">4. SCREENSHOT</h2>
<p data-start="1985" data-end="2006">Take a screenshot of:</p>
<ul data-start="2007" data-end="2080">
<li data-start="2007" data-end="2025">
<p data-start="2009" data-end="2025">the search query</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2026" data-end="2039">
<p data-start="2028" data-end="2039">the results</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2040" data-end="2060">
<p data-start="2042" data-end="2060">visible host names</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2061" data-end="2080">
<p data-start="2063" data-end="2080">visible Event IDs</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="2082" data-end="2102">Screenshot name:</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2103" data-end="2171"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>stage3-step3-2-security-log-verification.png</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="2173" data-end="2176">
<h2 data-start="2178" data-end="2195">5. SOC MEANING</h2>
<p data-start="2197" data-end="2232">This is an important analyst check.</p>
<p data-start="2234" data-end="2326">A SOC analyst never jumps to conclusions.<br data-start="2275" data-end="2278">
When one event is missing, the next question is:</p>
<ul data-start="2328" data-end="2400">
<li data-start="2328" data-end="2356">
<p data-start="2330" data-end="2356">Are logs missing entirely?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2357" data-end="2400">
<p data-start="2359" data-end="2400">Or is only one category of event missing?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2402" data-end="2448">That difference tells us whether the issue is:</p>
<ul data-start="2449" data-end="2500">
<li data-start="2449" data-end="2472">
<p data-start="2451" data-end="2472"><strong data-start="2451" data-end="2469">data ingestion</strong><br>
or</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2473" data-end="2500">
<p data-start="2475" data-end="2500"><strong data-start="2475" data-end="2500">logging configuration</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="2502" data-end="2546">This is real detection engineering thinking.</p>
<hr data-start="2548" data-end="2551">
<h2 data-start="2553" data-end="2577">6. INVESTIGATION NOTE</h2>
<p data-start="2579" data-end="2627">Copy this into <code data-start="2594" data-end="2618">investigation_notes.md</code> for now:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2629" data-end="3739"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>## Step 3.1 — Verification of Event ID 4688 in Splunk</span><br><br><span>### Action Performed</span><br><span>Searched Splunk for Windows Security Event ID 4688 using:</span><br><span>`index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security EventID=4688`</span><br><br><span>### Purpose</span><br><span>To verify whether process creation logs were being ingested into Splunk from Windows systems in the lab.</span><br><br><span>### Result</span><br><span>The search returned 0 events.</span><br><br><span>### Initial Assessment</span><br><span>This suggests that either process creation auditing is not enabled on the Windows system, the logs are not being forwarded, the Splunk time range is incorrect, or Event ID 4688 is not currently being generated in the lab.</span><br><br><span>### SOC Meaning</span><br><span>Event ID 4688 is critical because it records new process creation on Windows systems. It is heavily used in SOC operations to detect suspicious execution activity such as PowerShell abuse, command prompt usage, malware execution, and reconnaissance commands.</span><br><br><span>### Analyst Observation</span><br><span>The absence of Event ID 4688 requires further verification to determine whether Windows Security logs are reaching Splunk at all, or whether only process creation auditing is missing.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3741" data-end="3744">
