<hr data-start="957" data-end="960">
<h1 data-start="962" data-end="988">WHAT EVENT ID 4688 MEANS</h1>
<p data-start="990" data-end="1014">Event ID <strong data-start="999" data-end="1007">4688</strong> means:</p>
<blockquote data-start="1016" data-end="1052">
<p data-start="1018" data-end="1052"><strong data-start="1018" data-end="1052">A new process has been created</strong></p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="1054" data-end="1142">In practical SOC terms, this tells us when a program starts running on a Windows system.</p>
<p data-start="1144" data-end="1153">Examples:</p>
<ul data-start="1154" data-end="1278">
<li data-start="1154" data-end="1172">
<p data-start="1156" data-end="1172"><code data-start="1156" data-end="1172">powershell.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1173" data-end="1184">
<p data-start="1175" data-end="1184"><code data-start="1175" data-end="1184">cmd.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1185" data-end="1199">
<p data-start="1187" data-end="1199"><code data-start="1187" data-end="1199">whoami.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1200" data-end="1211">
<p data-start="1202" data-end="1211"><code data-start="1202" data-end="1211">net.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1212" data-end="1228">
<p data-start="1214" data-end="1228"><code data-start="1214" data-end="1228">ipconfig.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1229" data-end="1245">
<p data-start="1231" data-end="1245"><code data-start="1231" data-end="1245">rundll32.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1246" data-end="1278">
<p data-start="1248" data-end="1278">suspicious malware executables</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1280" data-end="1364">This is powerful because attackers must execute tools and commands during an attack.</p>
<hr data-start="1366" data-end="1369">
<h1 data-start="1371" data-end="1400">WHY THIS EVENT IS IMPORTANT</h1>
<p data-start="1402" data-end="1445">A SOC analyst uses Event ID 4688 to detect:</p>
<ul data-start="1447" data-end="1604">
<li data-start="1447" data-end="1475">
<p data-start="1449" data-end="1475">malicious PowerShell usage</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1476" data-end="1498">
<p data-start="1478" data-end="1498">command prompt abuse</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1499" data-end="1524">
<p data-start="1501" data-end="1524">reconnaissance commands</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1525" data-end="1543">
<p data-start="1527" data-end="1543">suspicious tools</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1544" data-end="1563">
<p data-start="1546" data-end="1563">malware execution</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1564" data-end="1604">
<p data-start="1566" data-end="1604">abnormal parent-child process behavior</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1606" data-end="1645">So this stage is about learning how to:</p>
<ul data-start="1646" data-end="1788">
<li data-start="1646" data-end="1664">
<p data-start="1648" data-end="1664">find 4688 events</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1665" data-end="1679">
<p data-start="1667" data-end="1679">inspect them</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1680" data-end="1709">
<p data-start="1682" data-end="1709">understand what process ran</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1710" data-end="1753">
<p data-start="1712" data-end="1753">decide whether it is normal or suspicious</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1754" data-end="1788">
<p data-start="1756" data-end="1788">document findings professionally</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="1790" data-end="1793">
