<p data-start="30" data-end="172">The key point is: <strong data-start="48" data-end="129">4688 exists somewhere in your Security logs, but your direct filter returns 0</strong>.<br data-start="130" data-end="133">
So we do one precise verification step.</p>
<h2 data-start="174" data-end="229">STEP 3.2 — Find the exact field name Splunk is using</h2>
<p data-start="231" data-end="240">Run this:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="242" data-end="328"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>spl</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security | top limit=20 EventID EventCode</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<h3 data-start="330" data-end="337">Why</h3>
<p data-start="338" data-end="360">Some Windows logs use:</p>
<ul data-start="361" data-end="389">
<li data-start="361" data-end="372">
<p data-start="363" data-end="372"><code data-start="363" data-end="372">EventID</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="373" data-end="389">
<p data-start="375" data-end="389">or <code data-start="378" data-end="389">EventCode</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="391" data-end="481">If <code data-start="394" data-end="400">4688</code> is stored in <code data-start="414" data-end="425">EventCode</code> instead of <code data-start="437" data-end="446">EventID</code>, your earlier search will miss it.</p>
<h2 data-start="483" data-end="503">What to send back</h2>
<p data-start="504" data-end="517">Just tell me:</p>
<ul data-start="518" data-end="587">
<li data-start="518" data-end="562">
<p data-start="520" data-end="562">whether <strong data-start="528" data-end="536">4688</strong> appears under <strong data-start="551" data-end="562">EventID</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="563" data-end="587">
<p data-start="565" data-end="587">or under <strong data-start="574" data-end="587">EventCode</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="589" data-end="610">Investigation note</h2>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="611" data-end="1052"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-lbtco6v1.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="w-full overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" style="transform: none; max-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>## Step 3.2 — Verify event field mapping</span><br><br><span>### Action Performed</span><br><span>Ran:</span><br><span>`index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security | top limit=20 EventID EventCode`</span><br><br><span>### Purpose</span><br><span>To confirm whether Splunk stores Windows event numbers in the `EventID` field or the `EventCode` field.</span><br><br><span>### SOC Meaning</span><br><span>Field validation is important in detection engineering because a wrong field name can make valid events appear missing even when the data exists.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
