<p data-start="199" data-end="218"><code data-start="199" data-end="218">index = lab_win10</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="219" data-end="274">
<p data-start="221" data-end="274"><code data-start="221" data-end="274">ParentProcessName = C:\Windows\System32\wininit.exe</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="275" data-end="325">
<p data-start="277" data-end="325"><code data-start="277" data-end="325">NewProcessName = C:\Windows\System32\lsass.exe</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="327" data-end="500">So Stage 3 is working. The reason your direct field search failed is that <strong data-start="401" data-end="461">Splunk is not extracting <code data-start="428" data-end="437">EventID</code> as a searchable field</strong>, even though it exists in the raw XML.</p>
