ax-height: 311px;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span>## Step 3.1 — Verifying Event ID 4688 Availability</span><br><br><span>The first step in Stage 3 was to verify whether Windows Security Event ID 4688 (process creation) was present in Splunk.</span><br><br><span>Initial direct field-based searches using `EventID=4688` and `EventCode=4688` returned 0 results. To validate whether the data still existed in another form, a raw text search was performed:</span><br><br><span>`index=* sourcetype=XmlWinEventLog:Security "4688"`</span><br><br><span>This returned results. One expanded event confirmed a valid XML-based Windows Security process creation record containing `&lt;EventID&gt;4688&lt;/EventID&gt;`.</span><br><br><span>The validated event was associated with:</span><br><span>- Host: `WIN10-CL01`</span><br><span>- Index: `lab_win10`</span><br><br><span>This step confirmed that the required process creation telemetry exists in the environment and can be used for further Stage 3 detection work.</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
